proguard.analysis.cpa.jvm.state.heap.tree

Class JvmTreeHeapPrincipalAbstractState

  • java.lang.Object
    • proguard.analysis.cpa.jvm.state.heap.tree.JvmTreeHeapAbstractState<SetAbstractState<Reference>>
      • proguard.analysis.cpa.jvm.state.heap.tree.JvmTreeHeapPrincipalAbstractState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    LatticeAbstractState<JvmHeapAbstractState<SetAbstractState<Reference>>>, AbstractState, JvmHeapAbstractState<SetAbstractState<Reference>>

    public class JvmTreeHeapPrincipalAbstractState
extends JvmTreeHeapAbstractState<SetAbstractState<Reference>>
    This is a self-sufficient heap model in the sense that it contains references necessary for addressing. When a memory location is accessed, it is created on-the-fly and is assumed to contain a distinct reference. Currently, such creation aliases all top level fields with deeper ones. For instance, if the object o is created on-the-fly, its field o.f will be aliased with o.f.f.
